LUMPY SKIN DISEASE, CATTLE - ERITREA
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 7 May 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information Vol 17- No. 19 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_46.HTM#Sec0>


Lumpy skin disease in Eritrea
-----------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of lumpy skin disease in Eritrea reported
to the OIE: October 2002).

Extract from the monthly report of Eritrea for February 2004,
received from Dr Ghebrehiwet Teame, Director of the Veterinary
Services Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Asmara:

No. of outbreaks in February 2004: 1

Location zoba of Gash, sub-zoba of Lalai Gash, locality of Ugumu (75
km west of Barentu):

Total number of animals in the outbreak:

species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered/
bov / 4000 / 16 / ... / .. / . .. /

Extract from the monthly report of Eritrea for March 2004, received
from Dr Ghebrehiwet Teame, Director of the Veterinary Services
Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Asmara:

No. of outbreaks in February 2004: 1

Location and locality of Azien (25 km north of Asmara)

Total number of animals in the outbreak:

species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed/ slaughtered/
bov / 50 / 2 / ... / ... / .. /

Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: To date, no
information for April 2004 has been received at the OIE Headquarters.

